           <div type="translation" source="bib:Chhom2011_01"><!-- kuch: The term 'slave' should be understood as 'servant'. -->
 	<p n="1-5"><gap reason="lost"/> 12 <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> baby girls (tai pau), <gap reason="lost"/> Tai <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/>, 3 girls at the age of running (tai rat), <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="5-7">The people from <gap reason="lost"/>: <gap reason="lost"/>, 7 male slaves (gho), <gap reason="lost"/> (glvā), <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="7-9"><gap reason="lost"/> Si Dharmmābhi-, <gap reason="lost"/>, 15 <gap reason="lost"/>, 69 female slaves (tai) <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="9-11"><gap reason="lost"/> 4 male slaves (gho), <gap reason="lost"/> female slaves (tai), <gap reason="lost"/>, 7 male slaves (gho), <gap reason="lost"/> animal keepers (gvāl), <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="11-12"><gap reason="lost"/> Si Jīva, <gap reason="lost"/> male slaves (gho), <gap reason="lost"/>, a baby; total <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="13-15">Sruk <gap reason="lost"/>, 7 <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/> boys at the age of running (si rat), <gap reason="lost"/>, a male slave (gho), <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="15-21">Ruined (inventory of two villages).</p>
              	<p n="21-25"><gap reason="lost"/>: Si <gap reason="lost"/>, <gap reason="lost"/>, 2 babies, <gap reason="lost"/>. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are 4 male slaves (gho), <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              	<p n="25-26"><gap reason="lost"/>, 3 male slaves (gho), an animal keeper (gvāl), <gap reason="lost"/>; total 11.</p>
              <p n="26-28">Sruk <gap reason="lost"/>, 8 male slaves (gho), 2 female slaves (tai); total <gap reason="lost"/>.</p>
              <p n="28-29">Sruk Rpā: Si Krau <gap reason="lost"/>; total 35. Among the <foreign>lvan</foreign>, there are <!-- kuch: The text may be continued in K.183-8. --></p>
                   </div> 
           <div type="commentary">
           <p>Wherever Chhom reads <foreign>pau</foreign> Jacques has <foreign>po</foreign>.</p>
